@node Autor "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Note from author:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    After  of  nime mouth, i can back to continue with my MSX2 emulator, now
with a MSX2 high quality emulation, but you need a good Amiga team.

    This  version  needs  AGA  chip  set.   version 2.2 was the last version
compatible  with  ORG/ECS  chip  set.  But future versions will work (in the
possible) with ORG/ECS chips.  (MC68020+ minimal requirred)

    This  new  version work more better than old versions.  But, please THIS
IS an emulator, NOT an MSX2 computer.

    New features of this version:

    - Line Interrupt emulation.

    YES!!!, Only Amiga makes it possible!!!  now you can play games like the
Aleste saga, Xevious, Mr.Ghost, Quarth, etc...  But CAUTION this need a good
Amiga  team  for  run  well.  (PAL screen and MSX2 Sprites refrest at 2fr is
recomended)


    - Sprites mode 2 emulation:

    Now MSX2 sprites are displayed with your right colours.

    There are 4 form to emulate:

    -  OFF :  MSX2 Sprites are not emulared.
    - 1 Fr.:  1 frame.  (100% refresh) too slow!
    - 2 Fr.:  2 frames. ( 50% refresh) Recomended.
    - 3 Fr.:  3 framas. ( 36% refresh) For Slow Amiga teams.

    Note:   MSX2 Sprites emulation is more slow.  For this reason some games
crash MSX2 emulation in 1fr.  mode.


    - Realtime emulations:

        - Line Interrupts.
        - Hardware Scroll.
        - Palette Changes.
        - Sprites display on/off
        - X Adjust of screen.


    - R-800 code supported, but not checked!!!!

    - Some Z-80A and VDP bugs fixed.

    - MSX Virtual Disk emulation.  (MVD:)

    - Cartridges emulation.  (Only Cartriges of 16/32Kb)

    - Cheat mode for find/set pokes of lives, level, etc...

    - Save Screen or complete VRAM as IFF-ILBM.  (Manga rulez!)


    and this is all by now.  I will you like my emulator!

    Finally, i can say...
       If you uses this software, regard you using a MSX2 computer.


                                         Juan Antonio G¾mez Gßlvez.

                                       (Barcelona 27 of May of 1996)


    PS:  Only AMIGA technology does it possible!

    PS2: Sorry my bad English.

@endnode


@node Introduccio "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Introduction
@{fg text}    ------------

    This program emulates an 8-bit MSX2 computer.

    Quality of emulation depens of the Amiga team that is used.

    This  program is not multitask and freezes the Operaty System for obtain
a good quality emulation programming directly the Amiga's custom chips.

    THIS  SHAREWARE  VERSION is freely distributable and can be published in
magazines and other circulation forms.  Allways that the all next files will
be included:

    AmiMSX2_v2.3              MSX2 Emulator.
    Keyboard.iff              Picture with MSX2 keys in the Amiga keyboard.
    MVD_Control               AmiMSX2 menu without MSX2 Emulation.

    MSX_Drivers/
     RAMSX:                   For mount a StaticRAD for MSX and Amiga.

    Docs/
     AmiMSX2_English.guide    This file.
     AmiMSX2_Espa±ol.guide    Original in Spanish of this file.

    #?.info                   Workbench's icons.


@{fg highlight}    DISCLAIMER:
@{fg text}    -----------
    THE AUTHOR DOESN'T GUARANTEE THAT THIS PROGRAM EMULATES A FULL MSX2,
AND ACCEPTS NO RESPONSABILITY FOR LOSS OF DATA DERIVED FROM THE USE OF
THIS SOFTWARE...

@endnode


@node Requeriments "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Requerimiens:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    - AMIGA computer with AGA chip set.
    - MC68020.
    - DEVS:mfm.device           (For DiskDrivers emulation)
    - DEVS:statram.device       (For RAMSX: drive emulation)
    - LIBS:stc020.library v3.0+
    - LIBS:asl.library
    - 3MB of memory (1Mb Chip)
    - PAL, NTSC or compatible monitor.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Minimal requeriments for real emulation:
@{fg text}    ---------------------------------------------

    - MC68020 at 28Mz  or  MC68030 at 25Mz
    - 2Mb of Fast32bit memory.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  compatibility:
@{fg text}    -------------------

    - 100% compatible with MC68020/MC68030/MC68040

    -  90% compatible with MC68060

    Note:  Traza0 mode (T0, bit 6 of SR) Don't work in MC68060.

@endnode


