@node MenuPro "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Project Menu:
@{fg text}    -------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> About:
@{fg text}    ----------

    Information about author and collaborators.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Menu Screen:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Set menu screen in PAL or NTSC.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save Screen:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Save the emulated screen like a IFF-ILBM file.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Cheat mode:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    For find/set Cheat pokes in the MSX2 emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save Prefs:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    Save preferences and MSX2 clock battery in S:MSX2emulator.prefs

@{fg highlight}    <*> Quit:
@{fg text}    ---------

    For quit the emulator.

@endnode

@node MenuOpt "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Options menu:
@{fg text}    -------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> JoyStick 2 ON:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    For activate emulation of second MSX Joystick.  (it will be connected in
the Amiga's mouse conector)

    Note:  This menu need be disabled for MSX mouse emulation.

    Caution:   if  this  menu  is activated and your amiga mouse is conected
some games will not work well.

@{fg highlight}             (JoySticks emulation in registered versions only)
@{fg text}

@{fg highlight}    <*> Multi-key ON:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    There  is  a  bug in Amiga 1200 keyboard, and some keys can't be pressed
together.   To  solve this, you can active this menu and then press all keys
you  want  separately.  MSX rom will think that you are pressing all keys at
the same time until you disables this menu.

@{fg highlight}    <*> DEL for Pause:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    Amiga's DEL key will be pause the emulation if this menu is enable.
    To exit of pause press DEL key again.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Ask for Go!:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    If this menu is enable ask for start the emulation when click GO.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Write Protected:
@{fg text}    --------------------

    If it is enabled, disk in MVD:  will be write-protected.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Sprites Base 2:
@{fg text}    -------------------

    Some games the MSX2 sprites are not displayed well, enable this men· for
solve.

    Note:  Only activate this menu then be necessary.

@{fg highlight}    <*> L. y R.Shift as Space:
@{fg text}    --------------------------

    Will  emulate  Left or Right Shift keys as Space.  (For sove A1200 Space
and Down key bug)

@endnode

@node MenuMVD "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    MSX Virtual Drive menu:
@{fg text}    -----------------------

    Now AmiMSX2 Emulator support a MSX Virtual Drive in Amiga's RAM.

    You  can  have Amiga files of 360Kb (1DD) or 720Kb (2DD) chunched as MSX
disks in your hard Disk, CD-ROM, etc...

    MVD  files can be crunched with Stone Cracker or File Imploder (suported
in emulator)

    Note:  MVD files are MSX Disk Images.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Load/Save Disk File:
@{fg text}    ------------------------

    For Load/Save MVD files.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Load/Save MSX Disk:
@{fg text}    -----------------------

    For Load/Save from/to MSX Disk.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Install MSX Boot:
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    For install MSX boot in MSX Disks.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Implode MVD:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Will crunch the resident MVD with File Imploder.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Format MVD as 2DD or 1DD:
@{fg text}    -----------------------------

    Create a bufer (MVD:) of 1DD/2DD MSX disk.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Clear Buffer:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    Clear bufer MVD:  (as an Eject disk of MVD:  drive)

@endnode

@node MenuCar "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Cartridges:
@{fg text}    -----------

    This is for simulate Cartridges of 16/32Kb.

    Slot  3  is  for  obtain  cartridges files but it is a bit complicate to
explain!

@{fg highlight}    Slot 1 y 2:
@{fg text}    -----------

    - Insert Cartridge: For read a cartridge file.

    - Eject Cartridge:  For eject the cartridge file readed.

    - ROM memory:       Emulation of ROM/RAM of cartridge memory.

@{fg highlight}    Slot 3:
@{fg text}    -------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save Pages:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    - Page 1:  Save Page 1 of Slot 3 (&H4000-&H7FFF)

    - Page 2:  Save Page 2 of Slot 3 (&H8000-&HBFFF)

    - Page 1 & 2:  Save Pages 1 and 2 of Slot 3 (&H4000-&HBFFF)

@endnode

@node FinestraPrin "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Ventana Principal:
@{fg text}    ------------------

@{fg highlight}    Disk Drivers:
@{fg text}    -------------

    With this gadgets you select which Amiga-diskdrives will be used to
emulate MSX drives A: and B: . If both A: and B: drives are OFF, MSX Disk
Basic ROM will not be emulated.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  MSX Drive A y B:
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    - DFx:   Emulation of Amiga drives.

    - MVD:   Emulation of @{"MSX Virtual Drive" link MenuMVD} (MVD:)

    - RAMSX: Emulation of Amigas's RAD as a MSX disk. (look @{"RAMSX:" link RAMSX})

    - OFF:   Emulation of NO drive connected.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  MSX Disk ROM:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    - DOS:   Emulation of Disk ROM v1.0

    - DOS2:  Emulation of Disk ROM v2.0

    - None:  Emulation of NO Disk ROM.

@{fg highlight}    Slots Options:
@{fg text}    --------------

@{fg highlight}    <*>  ROM:
@{fg text}    ---------

    - MSX:  Emulation of MSX ROM.

    - MSX2: Emulation of MSX2 ROM.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  RAM:
@{fg text}    ---------

    - Emulation of 128 to 4096Kb RAM.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Sound:
@{fg text}    -----------

    - PSG:  Emulation of PSG.

    - SCC:  Emulation of Konami's SCC.

    - SCC+: Emulation of Konami's SCC+.


@{fg highlight}    VDP Options:
@{fg text}    ------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Screen:
@{fg text}    -----------

    -  "Screen" selects display mode.

         * (MSX Mode) MSX will select NTSC or PAL when required.
         * (WB mode) MSX won't be able to exchange display mode.
         * PAL (50 Hz) The emulator will always run in PAL mode.
         * NTSC (60 Hz) The emulator will always run in NTSC mode.

    Note: PAL recommended.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Inter:
@{fg text}    ----------

    Set number of MSX vblank and line interrupts.

@{fg highlight}    <*> MSX2 Sprites:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    MSX2 Sprites refresh:

    - OFF: Not emulated.

    - 1fr: Refresh at 1 frame. (100%)

    - 2fr: Refresh at 2 frame.  (50%)

    - 3fr: Refresh at 3 frame.  (36%)

    Note: 2fr. recommended.

@{fg highlight}    Resto de Gadgets:
@{fg text}    ----------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> MVD:
@{fg text}    --------

    For read an MSX Virtual Disk in MVD:

@{fg highlight}    <*> Speed:
@{fg text}    ----------

    If a game works too fast just put this slider to a biger value.

    Note: Only when be necessary.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Slot 1 and 2:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    For read a cartridge file in any Slot.

@{fg highlight}    About:
@{fg text}    ------

    Equal than About menu.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Go!:
@{fg text}    --------

    For Start MSX emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Continue:
@{fg text}    -------------

    For continue emulation after of pressed HELP key.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Exit:
@{fg text}    ---------

    For quit emulator.

@endnode

@node FinestraIMP "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Imploder window:
@{fg text}    ----------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Implode:
@{fg text}    ------------

    For crunch resident MSX Virtual Disk in MVD:

@{fg highlight}    <*> Efficiency:
@{fg text}    ----------------------

    Compression efficiency.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Abort
@{fg text}    ---------

    Not implemented!

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save:
@{fg text}    ---------

    For save MVD crunched.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Cancel:
@{fg text}    -----------

    For exit to main menu.

@endnode

@node FinestraPoke "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Cheat window:
@{fg text}    -------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Find Poke:
@{fg text}    --------------

    This is for find cheat address.

    First set the actual lives in Searh for.
    Go to emulation and die one live.
    Go to this window and set the actual lives in Compare With.
    Now, in Address Found, you can find a possible lives address!

@{fg highlight}    <*> Poke:
@{fg text}    ---------

    When click Do poke, a poke is done in MSX memory.

                           ( Poke Address,Vaule )

    Some cheat poke Address:
    ------------------------
GORBY'S PIPELINE:       LEVEL=$C80C (INS 1-8) : PIPES=$C80D (DEL ONCE)
NYANACLE:               LIVES=$D215  TIME=$D214
