@node RAMSX "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    RAMSX: drive.
@{fg text}    -------------

    RAMSX:  is a drive for emulate a MSX disk using an Amiga's RAD.

    For use, you need mount it.  (like PCx:)

    Now  you can save files from WorkBench to RAMSX:  and read this files in
the emulator.

    Note: If you saves files from the emulator. You need do:

    DiskChange RAMSX:

    Now Amiga can read RAMSX: well.

    Note:  RAMSX:  uses StaticRAM.devive and not ramdrive!!!

@endnode


