@node Z80A "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Z-80A  (Procesador)
@{fg text}    -------------------

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Z-80A  (Processor)   Emulated at a 98%
@{fg text}    -----------------------
    All works correctly except this:

    - Flags N and H are not emulated.
    - SP register cannot read from ROM!
    - Flag P is only emulated at instructions OR, AND, XOR.
    - R register not emulated well.

    Now AMIGA NEVER can crash!

@endnode


@node Dibuixos "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    VDP  (Graphics chip)
@{fg text}    --------------------

    Emulated at a 85%.

    All works correctly except this:

    * Sprites:
        - Expanded Sprites.
        - Sprites Collisions.

    * VDP Commands:
        - MULTI mode (Screen 3)
        - Vertical Screen adjust.

    * MSX-Video:
        - XOR mode emulated as NOT.
        - Line logical operators.
        - Color search.

@endnode

@node Soroll "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  PSG  (Sound Chip)   Emulated at a 99%
@{fg text}    ----------------------
    It works correctly.


@{fg highlight}    <*>  SCC  (Sound Creator)   Emulated at 98%.
@{fg text}    -------------------------
    Amiga cannot emulate it correctly:

    -  SCC  chip  have 5 channels and Amiga only 4, when it uses 5 channels,
channel 5 will not emulated.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  SCC+  (Sound Creator)   Emulated at 98%.
@{fg text}    --------------------------
    Equal than SCC.

@endnode

@node Jocs "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Joystick ports.
@{fg text}    --------------------

    Two firebuttons in MSX are supported. Left Amiga and Right Amiga keys
work like joystick second firebutton.

    A Joypad can be used.

    Amiga firebutton 1 = MSX firebutton 1
    Amiga firebutton 2 & 3 = MSX firebutton 2    

    Amiga A port = MSX B port
    Amiga B port = MSX A port

              (JoySticks emulated in registered versions only)

@{fg highlight}    <*> Mouse.
@{fg text}    ----------

    MSX mouse is emulated in port A of MSX when Joystick 2 menu is disabled.

    Amiga mouse need be connected in port A of Amiga.

@endnode

@node Teclat "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Keyboard.   Emulated at a 99%
@{fg text}    --------------

    MSX keyboard is the same than Amiga's except the following keys:
    (English keymap only)

                          AMIGA       MSX
                         -------     -----
                            F6       SELECT
                            F7       STOP
                            F8       HOME/CLS
                            F9       INS
                           F10       DEL
                      Left ALT       GRAPH
                     Right ALT       CODE

                            ` ~      ± č  (In MSX2 ROM only)
                            DEL      MSX DEL or MSX Pause (optional)
                            [ {      Caps Lock.
                            < >      Caps Lock.
                            ń Ū      Dead key. (accents)
                            ] }      Dead key. (accents)

                     Left Amiga      JoyStick 1 - 2nd firebutton
                    Right Amiga      JoyStick 2 - 2nd firebutton

             CTRL+Left ALT+DEL       MSX Reset
             CTRL+Left ALT+HELP      MSX Hard Reset

                           HELP      Go to Workbench's menu. (Exit)


    Note:  č or ± is a Spanish letter.

@endnode

@node Disc "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Disk drive.  Emulated at a 99%
@{fg text}    ----------------

    For  a  good  emulation of MSX drivers you need mount PCx:  of the drive
that you are using.

    Note:  If PCx:  is not mounted 1DD MSX disks will fail!

    Make sure your disks have got a MSX boot to avoid a hang up when the
MSX is booting from a disk drive. You can install it in menu, using "MSX
Boot" gadget.
    DO NOT INSTALL ALL DISKS you get, because some MSX disks had their own
boot to run the game. Install only disks that you've formatted in a PC or
using PCx: drives.

    To emulate MSX disk drives I have had to "kill" the interrupt that
warns the Amiga that a disk has been changed, so when you exit the emulator
the diskdrive will not recognise Amiga disks. I am sorry.

    But you can do this for recover Amiga drivers:

    ASSIGN DFx: dismount
    MOUNT DFx:

    You need do a mount-list with DFx:  datas.

@endnode

@node Altres "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Memory.
@{fg text}    ------------
    You can emulate from 128 to 4096Kb RAM amd 128Kb VRAM.

    Sub-Slots (&HFFFF) are not supported, so there are NO COMPATIBILITY
PROBLEMS with Sony or Philips memory models!

    If you get a "out of memory" error, try to disable drive B: emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Clock Battery
@{fg text}    ------------------
    Correctly emulated except the time!  (┐?)


@{fg highlight}    <*>  Printer port.
@{fg text}    ------------------
    Emulated  at  a  99%.   Emulated  by  Sergi  Martinez.  (I haven't got a
printer!)

@endnode





@node incompatibilitat "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Errors and incompatibility.
@{fg text}    ---------------------------

    This  version  is very reliable, if any game don't work it can be an MSX
incompatibility.

    Try to do it:

    - Set to OFF or ON B: Disk-Drive.
    - Set 256Kb de RAM.
    - Set DOS or DOS2.
    - Set Screen to PAL.
    - Set MSX2 Sprites to 2fr. or 3fr.

    If  not  work  then  sorry,  wait for future versions or check in a real
MSX2.

@endnode


@node Tecnics "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Datos tķcnicos.
@{fg text}    ---------------

    This  program  was  developed  100%  in  assembly  language in one AMIGA
1200+Blizzard 1220 (MC68020 at 28Mz and 4Mb of Fast32bit RAM)

    For  do  a Hight Quality emulation this program disables Amiga multitask
and program Amiga's custom chips directly.

    The MSX2 used for check is a MSX2 Philips NMS-8280.

    All sources of this emulator was designed and programmed by the author.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Slots Configuration:
@{fg text}    ------------------------

                       Slot 0  Slot 1  Slot 2  Slot 3
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 0 | Bios  |       | Sub   |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 1 | Basic |       | Disk  |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 2 |       |       |       |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 3 |       |       |       |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|


@{fg highlight}    <*> Speed emulation:  (▒5%)
@{fg text}    ---------------------------

              Team              Time     Z-80A       %      Acelerator
      ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------
      MSX2  Philips NMS-8280     864     3.5Mz     100%
      ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------
      Amiga 1200/20  28Mz.       600     5.0Mz     144%    Blizzard 1220
      Amiga 1200/60  50Mz.       136    22.2Mz     635%    Blizzard 1260
      ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------

@endnode


@node Futur "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Future versions:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Now,  I  will  dedicate  minus time to develope my emulator for personal
problems.

    For this cause i don't know when ending version 2.4

    * Features for version 2.4:

    -   MSX-Video   emulation   (MSX2   blitter)   in   real  multitask  and
super-optimized CPU-VRAM modes and viceversa.

    For this cause, some games like Zanac-Ex don't work well.

    - 100% Actualization of VRAM (Amiga Bit-planes) in Screen changes.

    For this cause, some games like Feed Back don't work well.


    * Emulation in longer term:

    -  Emulation  of  Graph 3 and 4 in real-time for a possible emulation of
Space Manbow.

    - FM Pak emulation via MIDI.

    - Compatibility with ORG/ECS chips.

    - More compatibility with MC68060.

@endnode


